r49764 | claus@wildside.dk | 2011-07-12 18:31:57 +0200 (Tue, 12 Jul 2011) | 18 lines

[FEATURE] First iteration of Fluid Page Rendering feature

Does not currently support a lot of features; can render one 
single Fluid template as a site design templat at this time.

Next iteration will feature selection of the "Controller action" 
which is run on the "Page" controller - in other words, turning 
TYPO3's page rendering into an MVC module using BE-layouts to 
guide content and extended fields to select the FE rendering 
template file.

Supports Partials and Layouts, too. Path to page templates can 
be defined through TypoScript, allowing extensions to provide 
the page templating along with Fluid FCEs and the usual MVC.

A complete reference will be provided on the doc. web site.


