r49610 | claus@wildside.dk | 2011-07-07 22:45:45 +0200 (Thu, 07 Jul 2011) | 18 lines

[FEATURE] Began work on HashController

PLEASE BE AWARE THAT THIS HAS SECURITY IMPLICATIONS 
WHEN USED! YOU SHOULD -NEVER- ADD THIS PLUGIN ON PUBLIC 
PAGES - ALLOW ACCESS FOR ONLY VERIFIED USERS!

This Controller will let you "sign" dynamic form fields with 
your site's encryption key, allowing you to dynamically change the 
hmac checksum of Extbase forms (using a shortly incoming JS util).

To work this, insert a "general plugin" of FED Hasher on the page 
which renders your dynamic form. Using the Javascript util your 
form will be parsed and corrected - and a call will be made to the 
exact same page, asking for a HMAC checksum.

I repeat: NEVER USE THIS ON UNPROTECTED PAGES!


------------------------------------------------------------------------
r49609 | claus@wildside.dk | 2011-07-07 22:35:33 +0200 (Thu, 07 Jul 2011) | 2 lines

[FEATURE] Added the ExposedTemplateView class - see previous commit msg.

------------------------------------------------------------------------
r49608 | claus@wildside.dk | 2011-07-07 22:34:24 +0200 (Thu, 07 Jul 2011) | 14 lines

[FEATURE] Added ExposedTemplateView which can access info after rendering

The FlexibleContentElementView now extends this and only adds the 
getFlexibleContentElementDefinitions method

You can use this ExposedTemplateView for emails, among other things, 
by registering subjects etc. using vars: fed:data.var name="subject" 
and then $template->harvest('subject'); from where you started rendering 

Currently only supports "harvest" method which gets a single variable, but 
will shortly be extended with a lot more methods to harvest a lot more 
details about the template rendering context and variables.


