r48500 | claus@wildside.dk | 2011-06-09 20:33:13 +0200 (Thu, 09 Jun 2011) | 13 lines

[TASK] Improved ExtJS4 Template parsing using custom pattern

A special pattern which disregards { } notations in Fluid if 
they are found to contain spaces was implemented - this to 
allow un-escaped notations of complex object structures in 
a Fluid template without having to repeatedly use 
f:format.escape on nested curly braces.

The original pattern is restored immediately after parsing 
and does not affect Fluid parsing - but does affect any 
nested ViewHelper call you use in your ExtJS4 Model.js


